<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFSummers1996">Summers, Montague (1996) [1929]. <i>The Vampire in Europe</i>. Gramercy Books: New York. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0517149893" class="internal">ISBN 0-517-14989-3</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Vampire+in+Europe&amp;rft.aulast=Summers&amp;rft.aufirst=Montague&amp;rft.au=Summers%2C+Montague&amp;rft.date=1996&amp;rft.place=Gramercy+Books&amp;rft.pub=New+York&amp;rft.isbn=0-517-14989-3&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Vampire"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span> (also published as <i>The Vampire in Lore and Legend</i>, <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0486419428" class="internal">ISBN 0-486-41942-8</a>)</li>
<li><span class="languageicon" style="font-size:0.95em; font-weight:bold; color:#555;">(Serbian)</span> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFVukovi.C4.872004">Vuković, Milan T. (2004). <i>Народни обичаји, веровања и пословице код Срба</i>. Belgrade: Сазвежђа. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/8683699080" class="internal">ISBN 86-83699-08-0</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=%D0%9D%D0%B0%D1%80%D0%BE%D0%B4%D0%BD%D0%B8+%D0%BE%D0%B1%D0%B8%D1%87%D0%B0%D1%98%D0%B8%2C+%D0%B2%D0%B5%D1%80%D0%BE%D0%B2%D0%B0%D1%9A%D0%B0+%D0%B8+%D0%BF%D0%BE%D1%81%D0%BB%D0%BE%D0%B2%D0%B8%D1%86%D0%B5+%D0%BA%D0%BE%D0%B4+%D0%A1%D1%80%D0%B1%D0%B0&amp;rft.aulast=Vukovi%C4%87&amp;rft.aufirst=Milan+T.&amp;rft.au=Vukovi%C4%87%2C+Milan+T.&amp;rft.date=2004&amp;rft.place=Belgrade&amp;rft.pub=%D0%A1%D0%B0%D0%B7%D0%B2%D0%B5%D0%B6%D1%92%D0%B0&amp;rft.isbn=86-83699-08-0&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Vampire"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFWright1973">Wright, Dudley (1973) [1914]. <i>The Book of Vampires</i>. New York: Causeway Books. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0883560070" class="internal">ISBN 0-88356-007-0</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Book+of+Vampires&amp;rft.aulast=Wright&amp;rft.aufirst=Dudley&amp;rft.au=Wright%2C+Dudley&amp;rft.date=1973&amp;rft.place=New+York&amp;rft.pub=Causeway+Books&amp;rft.isbn=0-88356-007-0&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Vampire"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span> (Originally published as <i>Vampire and Vampirism</i>; also published as <i>The History of Vampires</i>)</li>
